Here's a PlantUML sequence diagram focusing on the scheduling and control flow aspects of the Marlowe Starter Kit:

```plantuml
@startuml input-output-hk_marlowe-starter-kit

actor User
participant "Jupyter Notebook" as Notebook
participant "Controller.js" as Controller
participant "Wallet (CIP30/45)" as Wallet
participant "Marlowe Runtime" as Runtime
participant "Cardano Blockchain" as Blockchain

User -> Notebook: Executes lesson (e.g., escrow)
Notebook -> Runtime: Query contract templates
Runtime --> Notebook: Return templates
Notebook -> Controller: Initialize UI components
Controller -> Wallet: Connect wallet request
Wallet --> Controller: Connection established
Controller -> Wallet: Request addresses
Wallet --> Controller: Return addresses

alt Contract Creation
    User -> Controller: Submit contract parameters
    Controller -> Runtime: Create contract draft
    Runtime --> Controller: Return draft Tx
    Controller -> Wallet: Sign draft transaction
    Wallet --> Controller: Signed Tx
    Controller -> Runtime: Submit signed Tx
    Runtime -> Blockchain: Post transaction
    Blockchain --> Runtime: Tx confirmation
    Runtime --> Controller: Contract ID
    Controller --> User: Display contract status
end

loop Monitoring
    Controller -> Runtime: Poll contract state
    Runtime --> Controller: Return current state
    Controller --> User: Update UI
end

alt Contract Execution
    User -> Controller: Trigger action (e.g., deposit)
    Controller -> Runtime: Prepare action Tx
    Runtime --> Controller: Return action Tx
    Controller -> Wallet: Sign action Tx
    Wallet --> Controller: Signed Tx
    Controller -> Runtime: Submit signed Tx
    Runtime -> Blockchain: Post transaction
    Blockchain --> Runtime: Tx confirmation
    Runtime --> Controller: Updated state
    Controller --> User: Display result
end

@enduml
```